Class Model

java.lang.Object
Model
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Model
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Where all the raw data of the program goes from the GardenPlot which holds GardenTiles which have attributes such as sunlight received and soil wetness. Furthermore the GardenTiles hold an AddOn or Plant with their own attributes.
Author:
Malachi Parks

    • filterByColor

      public java.util.ArrayList<Plant> filterByColor​(java.util.ArrayList<Plant> a, java.lang.String color)
      Takes in an ArrayList a, which represents the arrayList being sorted while the color param is the usersColor pref attribute which was obtained from the preferences of view passing in userinput.

      Used to filter an array of plants by color. First iterates of the array and adds all the plants that don't match the otherColorArr then filters using a stream, iterating over using a lambda then returning true items to the stream.

      Parameters:
      a - is the arrayList to be sorted
      color - the users color preferenced passed in by Controller from Preferences
      Returns:
      a filtered ArrayList by Plant color

    • filterByWater

      public java.util.ArrayList<Plant> filterByWater​(java.util.ArrayList<Plant> a, int waterReq)
      Takes in an ArrayList a, which represents the arrayList being sorted while the waterReq param is the usersWaterPref attribute which was obtained from the preferences of view passing in userinput.

      Used to filter an array of plants by waterReq. First takes in the waterReq into a switchStatement and creates a high and low bound to add to when filtering. Then adds all the plants that don't meet the waterRange to the otherWater Arr finally sorts the array by the range and returns it

      Parameters:
      a - is the arrayList to be sorted
      waterReq - is the amount of water a plant needs
      Returns:
      a filtered ArrayList by Plant waterReq

    • filterByType

      public java.util.ArrayList<Plant> filterByType​(java.util.ArrayList<Plant> a, java.lang.String type)
      Takes in an ArrayList a, which represents the arrayList being sorted while the type param which is the kind of plant it is (Shrub, Tree, Flower, UnderGrowth) Called in each of hte update methods to set up the inital arrays

    • getRecs

      public java.lang.String getRecs​(int x, int y)

      Parameters:

      Returns:
